## 2026-04-03 - Command palette has no "jump to next validation issue" action
- Added `jumpToNextIssue` callback in App.tsx that cycles through `lintViolations` (from `useLint` for the active set) using a `lintIssueIndexRef` ref. On each call it increments the index (with wrap-around), navigates to 'define'/'tokens', calls `setHighlightedToken(path)` to scroll/expand to the token, and shows a toast like "✗ Issue 2/5: <message>". The ref resets to -1 via a `useEffect` when `activeSet` changes so cycling restarts on set switch.
- Added F8 keyboard shortcut handler in the stable `keyboardShortcutRef.current` block.
- Added "Jump to Next Issue" command to the commands array (category: 'Tokens', shortcut: 'F8') with a live description showing the current violation count.

